race.comment: MACY MOON (5) showed little early dash last start but finished full of running to grab third, beaten 2L by GREY LAD here last start. Strips fitter third-up and gets a nice swing at the weights over the winner. Backing he turns the tables. GREY LAD (3) is in top form, making it three wins from his last four starts at the latest. Has a strong association with Bent who partners again. Rises in the weights but is sure to be very competitive. ASEVENTY SEVEN (6) was comfortably accounted last time but was a barnstorming Moe winner the previous outing. Kept on the fresh side for this and can bounce back quickly. ALTROVE (7) failed to go on with the job here last time but her prior form stacks right up and her record at thus venue speaks for itself. Can put that poor run swiftly behind her. STAR BLAZER (1) is a tricky one to catch but is a two-time winner over this course and distances and gets help at the weights with the claimer engaged. Must for exotics.
